Bring 1 cup water, the @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, the @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @soy sauce{1%tbsp} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Cover and reduce to a simmer for ~{20%minutes}, until tender.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and discard the root end of the @baby bok choy{2}, before separating the leaves. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Halve the @lime{1}. Cut one half into wedges. Peel and grate the @ginger{1%thumb} into a paste. Grate the @garlic{2%cloves} into a paste. Alternatively, mince the garlic and ginger, then smash it against your cutting board with the side of your knife.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{1%jar}, a squeeze of lime, a pinch of garlic, a pinch of ginger, and some @wasabi paste{3%tsp}. (TIP: Add a little, taste, and then add more if desired.) Thin to a dressing-like consistency with 2-3 teaspoons water. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the scallion whites, remaining garlic, and remaining ginger to the pan. Cook ~{1-2%minutes}, until slightly golden. Add the bok choy and 1 Tablespoon water to the pan. Cook, tossing, until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from the pan and set aside, covered to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in the same pan over medium-high heat. Season the @skin-on salmon{12%oz} on all sides with salt and pepper. Add to the pan skin-side down. Cook ~{5-6%minutes}, until skin is crispy and golden brown. Reduce heat to medium, flip salmon, and cook ~{3-4%minutes}, until opaque.

Finish: Serve the crispy salmon and bok choy on a bed of soy-infused rice. Drizzle with the wasabi lime dressing, garnish with the scallion greens, and serve with a wedge of lime. Enjoy!